<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-10-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-10-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="591" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d591">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Major General <persName type="from">S. L.
                                    Howard</persName>, U. S. M. C., to the Commander of the Seventh
                                Fleet</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Cooke</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tientsin</hi>
                                </placeName>] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-10-23">23
                                    October 1946</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>220628Z. Executive Headquarters does not wish to send team into Tangku
                            area for rescue of two Marines. Request for rescue has been addressed to
                            both Nationalist and Communist representatives at Executive Hqs.
                            Nationalist Headquarters state they have initiated action. Communist
                            Hqs. state they will forward the request to Yenan.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>